results.name: Decimal expansion of sqrt(13)/3.
comment: Draw two congruent line segments inside the unit square from the same vertex of the square to opposite sides of the square. sqrt(13)/3 is the length of each line segment needed to dissect the square into 3 regions with equal areas.
results.author: _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, May 08 2021
